</ext_description>
<!-- +++++++++++ Assembly_requirement_allocation +++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Assembly_physical_requirement_allocation_arm.Assembly_requirement_allocation">
An <b>Assembly_requirement_allocation</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="Requirement_assignment:arm:Requirement_assignment_arm.Requirement_assignment"/>. 
An <b>Assembly_requirement_allocation</b> may be one or more of an <express_ref linkend="Assembly_physical_requirement_allocation:arm:Assembly_physical_requirement_allocation_arm.Assembly_separation_requirement_allocation"/>, an <express_ref linkend="Assembly_physical_requirement_allocation:arm:Assembly_physical_requirement_allocation_arm.Electromagnetic_compatibility_requirement_allocation"/>, or a <express_ref linkend="Assembly_physical_requirement_allocation:arm:Assembly_physical_requirement_allocation_arm.Thermal_requirement_allocation"/>. An 
<b>Assembly_requirement_allocation</b> is the relationship between the <express_ref linkend="Requirement_decomposition:arm:Requirement_decomposition_arm.Requirement_definition_property"/> and either an <express_ref linkend="Physical_unit_design_view:arm:Physical_unit_design_view_arm.Assembly_component"/> or a <express_ref linkend="Component_feature:arm:Component_feature_arm.Component_feature"/> that satisfies that  <express_ref linkend="Requirement_decomposition:arm:Requirement_decomposition_arm.Requirement_definition_property"/>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Assembly_physical_requirement_allocation_arm.Assembly_requirement_allocation.assigned_to">
an attribute inherited from  <express_ref linkend="Requirement_assignment:arm:Requirement_assignment_arm.Requirement_assignment"/> specifies either an <express_ref linkend="Physical_unit_design_view:arm:Physical_unit_design_view_arm.Assembly_component"/> or a <express_ref linkend="Component_feature:arm:Component_feature_arm.Component_feature"/> or an <express_ref linkend="Assembly_technology:arm:Assembly_technology_arm.Assembly_joint"/> for the <b>Assembly_requirement_allocation</b>.
</ext_description>
<!-- +++++++++++ Assembly_separation_requirement_allocation +++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Assembly_physical_requirement_allocation_arm.Assembly_separation_requirement_allocation"><p>
An <b>Assembly_separation_requirement_allocation</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="Assembly_physical_requirement_allocation:arm:Assembly_physical_requirement_allocation_arm.Assembly_requirement_allocation"/>. An <b>Assembly_separation_requirement_allocation</b> provides for the physical spacing required among components of the assembly.
The <b>Assembly_separation_requirement_allocation</b> is for the purpose of specifying separation between items based on the <express_ref linkend="Requirement_decomposition:arm:Requirement_decomposition_arm.Requirement_definition_property"/>. 
</p><note>
Multiple members of this entity may be populated in order to specify all the sets with which a given set 
will be disjoint, either thermally or electromagnetically.
</note>
<example>
A typical usage of this AO is to reference a member of <express_ref linkend="Fabrication_technology:arm:Fabrication_technology_arm.Layout_spacing_requirement_occurrence"/> as the requirement inherited from  <express_ref linkend="Assembly_physical_requirement_allocation:arm:Assembly_physical_requirement_allocation_arm.Assembly_requirement_allocation"/>.
</example>
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Assembly_physical_requirement_allocation_arm.Assembly_separation_requirement_allocation.disjoint_assignment">
specifies either an <express_ref linkend="Physical_unit_design_view:arm:Physical_unit_design_view_arm.Assembly_component"/> or a <express_ref linkend="Component_feature:arm:Component_feature_arm.Component_feature"/> for the <b>Assembly_separation_requirement_allocation</b>. There
shall be one or more  <express_ref linkend="Physical_unit_design_view:arm:Physical_unit_design_view_arm.Assembly_component"/> or  <express_ref linkend="Component_feature:arm:Component_feature_arm.Component_feature"/> for the <b>Assembly_separation_requirement_allocation</b>.  The <b>disjoint_assignment</b> shall be applied pairwise.
</ext_description>
<!-- +++++++++++ Electromagnetic_compatibility_requirement_allocation +++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Assembly_physical_requirement_allocation_arm.Electromagnetic_compatibility_requirement_allocation">

An <b>Electromagnetic_compatibility_requirement_allocation</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="Assembly_physical_requirement_allocation:arm:Assembly_physical_requirement_allocation_arm.Assembly_requirement_allocation"/>. An 
<b>Electromagnetic_compatibility_requirement_allocation</b> may be a <express_ref linkend="Assembly_physical_requirement_allocation:arm:Assembly_physical_requirement_allocation_arm.Shield_allocation"/>.
</ext_description>
<!-- +++++++++++ Interface_component_allocation +++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Assembly_physical_requirement_allocation_arm.Interface_component_allocation">

 An <b>Interface_component_allocation</b> is the assignment relationship 
between an <express_ref linkend="Interface_component:arm:Interface_component_arm.Interface_component"/> on an assembly and the <express_ref linkend="Assembly_physical_interface_requirement:arm:Assembly_physical_interface_requirement_arm.Mating_connector_component"/> to which the  <express_ref linkend="Interface_component:arm:Interface_component_arm.Interface_component"/> must mechanically and 
electrically mate in the next assembly level.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Assembly_physical_requirement_allocation_arm.Interface_component_allocation.mating_requirement">
specifies the role of the <express_ref linkend="Assembly_physical_interface_requirement:arm:Assembly_physical_interface_requirement_arm.Mating_connector_component"/> for the <b>Interface_component_allocation</b>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Assembly_physical_requirement_allocation_arm.Interface_component_allocation.mating_solution">
specifies the role of the <express_ref linkend="Interface_component:arm:Interface_component_arm.Interface_component"/> for the <b>Interface_component_allocation</b>.
</ext_description>
<!-- +++++++++++ Shield_allocation +++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Assembly_physical_requirement_allocation_arm.Shield_allocation">
<p>
A <b>Shield_allocation</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="Assembly_physical_requirement_allocation:arm:Assembly_physical_requirement_allocation_arm.Electromagnetic_compatibility_requirement_allocation"/>.
The <b>Shield_allocation</b> enables the assignment of a requirement to a shield.  
This allocates required properties of shielding effectiveness to the shield.  
</p>
<note> The text description for this Application Object has not been fully updated to agree with the EXPRESS.</note>
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Assembly_physical_requirement_allocation_arm.Shield_allocation.assigned_requirement">
specifies the role of the <express_ref linkend="Requirement_decomposition:arm:Requirement_decomposition_arm.Electromagnetic_requirement_occurrence"/> for the <b>Shield_allocation</b>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Assembly_physical_requirement_allocation_arm.Shield_allocation.assigned_to">
specifies the role of the <express_ref linkend="Shield:arm:Shield_arm.Shield"/> for the 
<b>Shield_allocation</b>.
</ext_description>
<!-- +++++++++++ Thermal_requirement_allocation +++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Assembly_physical_requirement_allocation_arm.Thermal_requirement_allocation">
A <b>Thermal_requirement_allocation</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="Assembly_physical_requirement_allocation:arm:Assembly_physical_requirement_allocation_arm.Assembly_requirement_allocation"/> for which the <express_ref linkend="Requirement_decomposition:arm:Requirement_decomposition_arm.Requirement_definition_property"/> has thermal 
characteristics. A 
<b>Thermal_requirement_allocation</b> is the relationship between the <express_ref linkend="Requirement_decomposition:arm:Requirement_decomposition_arm.Thermal_requirement_occurrence"/> and the <express_ref linkend="Physical_unit_design_view:arm:Physical_unit_design_view_arm.Thermal_component"/> that satisfies it.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Assembly_physical_requirement_allocation_arm.Thermal_requirement_allocation.assigned_requirement">
specifies the role of the <express_ref linkend="Requirement_decomposition:arm:Requirement_decomposition_arm.Thermal_requirement_occurrence"/> for the <b>Thermal_requirement_allocation</b>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Assembly_physical_requirement_allocation_arm.Thermal_requirement_allocation.assigned_to">
specifies the role of the <express_ref linkend="Physical_unit_design_view:arm:Physical_unit_design_view_arm.Thermal_component"/> for the <b>Thermal_requirement_allocation</b>.
</ext_description>
</ext_descriptions>

